= Readme Free Magazine Competition =
 =========================================

Note: This is just a quick guide to compile and run
the files under Ubuntu. In other distributions, it is similar.

Full details can be found on the website:

    http://www.freiesmagazin.de/programmierwettbewerb

and in the FAQ:

    http://www.freiesmagazin.de/20090409-programmierwettbewerb-faq

----------------------------------------------
1. Installation of the package "build-essential"
----------------------------------------------

sudo apt-get install build-essential

or

sudo aptitude install build-essential


----------------------------------------------
2. Compiling the files
----------------------------------------------

make

Note: Links ai1.bin fm and fm-ai2.bin show later on
Programs with the AI of the competitors. Usually occurs
not the same program against itself to.


----------------------------------------------
3a. Game Manual
----------------------------------------------

. / Fm-game-bin

run and at each break a file "result.dat" with the content
the playing fields to be exchanged to create. E.g.

6 8 5 8

emerged the field (6.8) with (5.8).


----------------------------------------------
3b. Playing field for competition to create
----------------------------------------------

. / Fm-game-bin create FILE NAME

The file name is for example "Game field-contest1.dat.


----------------------------------------------
3c. Competitive start
----------------------------------------------

. / Fm-game-bin FILE NAME

The file name is for example "Game field-contest1.dat.

First start player 1, then Player 2 with the same starting point.
The steps may include all traced in the output.